claim.claim-text:
1. An RFID device comprising:
an antenna structure having a sheet of electrically conductive material extending on both sides of an elongated slot; and
a wireless communication device having a pair of contact points electrically coupled to respective parts of the conductive material;
wherein the parts of conductive material are electrically coupled together at a first end of the elongated slot distal from the wireless communication device;
wherein a second end of the elongated slot is an open end, not short-circuited between the parts;
wherein the elongated slot has a slot length in a direction in which the slot is elongated, and a slot width in a direction perpendicular to the slot length; and
wherein the parts of conductive material extending on the sides of the slot along the slot length have a combined antenna width in the direction of the slot width that is greater than the slot width of the slot.

39. The method of claim 31, wherein, for each of the RFID devices:
the end of the elongated slot distal from the wireless communication device is a first end;
a second end of the elongated slot is an open end, not short-circuited between the parts;
the elongated slot has a slot length in a direction in which the slot is elongated, and a slot width in a direction perpendicular to the slot length; and
the parts of conductive material extending on the sides of the slot along the slot length have a combined antenna width in the direction of the slot width that is greater than the slot width of the slot.

43. An RFID device comprising:
an antenna structure having a sheet of electrically conductive material extending on both sides of an elongated slot; and
a wireless communication device having a pair of contact points electrically coupled to respective parts of the conductive material;
wherein the parts of conductive material are electrically coupled together at a first end of the elongated slot distal from the wireless communication device;
wherein a second end of the elongated slot is an open end, not short-circuited between the parts; and
wherein the parts are capacitively coupled together at the first end of the slot.
